DataElement.preferredName: Office for Human Research Protections Training Completion Date
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The date training provided by or for the office at the DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES that leads efforts for protecting human subjects in biomedical and behavioral research was completed.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Office for Human Research Protections Training
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Training provided by or for the office at the DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES that leads efforts for protecting human subjects in biomedical and behavioral research.

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: The office at the DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES that leads efforts for protecting human subjects in biomedical and behavioral research. It was created in 2000. It replaces the Office for Protection from Research Risks (OPRR), which was part of the National Institutes of Health (NIH) and had authority over NIH-funded research.
